    </div>

    <div class="findings">
      <h2>Key Screening Insights</h2>
      <div class="finding-card">
        <h3>Value Stocks Are Concentrated in Financials &amp; Healthcare</h3>
        <p>Stocks with PE ratios under 15 are predominantly found in financials (JPM, BAC, WFC) and healthcare (JNJ, PFE, ABBV). These sectors trade at discounts due to regulatory uncertainty and patent cliffs respectively — but offer yields above 2.5% and stable cash flows that attract income investors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-card">
        <h3>Tech Dominates 52-Week Outperformers</h3>
        <p>8 of the top 10 performers over the past 52 weeks are technology or communication stocks. NVDA leads at +68%, followed by META at +42%. However, most tech outperformers carry PE ratios above 30, meaning growth investors are paying premium valuations for continued momentum.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-card">
        <h3>Dividend Champions Show Lower Volatility</h3>
        <p>Stocks with 25+ years of consecutive dividend increases have averaged just 12% drawdowns in corrections vs. 22% for the broader S&amp;P 500. Companies like JNJ, PG, KO, and PEP combine yield with resilience — making them core holdings for conservative portfolios seeking steady income through market cycles.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div id="faq"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="related-section">
      <h2>Related Tools &amp; Research</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a class="related-card" href="/intrinsic-value-dashboard">
          <h3>Intrinsic Value Dashboard</h3>
          <p>Calculate fair value for any stock using DCF, Graham, and comparable analysis models.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="related-card" href="/dividend-etf-comparison">
          <h3>Dividend ETF Comparison</h3>
          <p>Compare 21 dividend ETFs side-by-side: SCHD, VYM, JEPI, QYLD &amp; more ranked by yield and returns.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="related-card" href="/ai-stock-dashboard">
          <h3>AI Stock Dashboard</h3>
          <p>Track AI sector stocks with real-time metrics, earnings, and competitive positioning analysis.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="methodology">
      <h2>Methodology</h2>
      <p>Stock data represents approximate values for 50 of the largest S&amp;P 500 companies as of Q1 2026. Market capitalizations, PE ratios, and dividend yields are based on trailing twelve-month figures sourced from public financial data. 52-week performance reflects price change only (excludes dividends).</p>
      <p>Preset screens use commonly accepted thresholds: Value Stocks (PE &lt; 20, yield &gt; 2%), Growth Stocks (52W change &gt; 20%, PE &gt; 20), Dividend Champions (25+ consecutive years of dividend increases), and Large Cap Leaders (market cap &gt; $500B). Screens are for educational purposes and do not constitute buy recommendations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="disclaimer">This tool provides data for informational and educational purposes only. Not investment advice. Stock data is approximate and may not reflect real-time prices. Always verify data before making investment decisions.</div>
</div>

